original:
The program, which operated for 90 years, concluded in 1970 due to the prioritization of emerging initiatives at the Patuxent Wildlife Research Center (PWRC). In 2009, the program was revived with the objective of digitizing its extensive collection of records. With the collaboration of citizens worldwide, each record is currently being transcribed into a publicly accessible database.

Notable contributions to this field were made by En
